@*
    DocCodeBlock — inline code block for Concepts and Guides pages where the
    code is illustrative (not from an anchored snippet file).

    Why this exists: Razor tries to parse `<` as a tag opener even inside
    <pre><code> blocks, so any C# sample with generics (List<Foo>), comparisons
    (x < 0), or HTML markup breaks the page with cryptic Razor errors. This
    helper takes the code as a string parameter — Razor sees it as data, not
    markup, so the < characters survive untouched.

    The output DOM matches what CodeViewer produces (a <pre class="line-numbers">
    with a <code class="language-X"> inside) so the Prism syntax-highlighting
    theme loaded globally also styles these blocks. We trigger Prism
    highlighting after render via JS interop — without this, the code renders
    as un-highlighted text and the dark theme's text colors leave it
    invisible-on-white.

    For verified, anchored code that comes from a real source file, use
    <DocSnippet Name="..." /> instead.
*@

@inject IJSRuntime JS

<pre class="line-numbers"><code class="language-@Language">@Code</code></pre>

@code {
    [Parameter, EditorRequired] public string Code { get; set; } = default!;
    [Parameter] public string Language { get; set; } = "csharp";

    protected override async Task OnAfterRenderAsync(bool firstRender)
    {
        // Re-run Prism on every render so navigation between pages picks up
        // newly-mounted code blocks. Prism's toolbar plugin attaches the
        // native Copy button automatically as part of highlighting. Cheap to
        // call repeatedly.
        await JS.InvokeVoidAsync("Prism.highlightAll");
    }
}
